<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO TOM DIER</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb 25 22:20:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Tom, I am surprised by your response. I raised the issues of good medals in a bad war as an honest question.  Why the attack?  I am not putting you, or anyone down, and I am not calling you a loyal fido, just raising the issue as we're all pawns in the game?  Seems like you are flaming at me out of proportion and I am confused by that.  I left my shrink credentials at the door, by the way, and am only trying to learn and grown like the rest of you.  They did not teach survivor and viet nam in therapy 1A, whether you were in bush or in bedpan. On the couch or under it.<br><br>
I ask you to reread my post. I did not label nor want to infer that you or anyone was &quot;loyal fido's&quot;. <br><br>
I am trying dearly to rethink most of my thoughs about veterans, alas, your out of left field jab wants me to retreat to what I USED to think was correct.   How odd, I just unloaded on Nurse Ratchet on #6 and I dial in here to catch it from you. Poetic Justice I guess.<br><br>
Do I ever wonder how I would react in combat you ask. Yes I do.  It scares the s.... out of me to tell the truth. I don't think I would have survived.  I have never put down the bravery involved in survival, only the leadership that created the situation.<br><br>
Am I missing something here Tom, if so please educate me, and I mean that sincerely.  My ego be damned, that, to me, is a thing of the past and long put to rest.  Why does a Nurse Ratchet so piss me off while a Wingman so confuses me?  Could you have misread me?  <br><br>
I see the smugness of a Nurse Ratchet at one end, the bravery of the grunt in the bush at the other. I am somewhere in the middle. Not like (equal is the wrong word) the medic-C.O. at all.  Not like those who fled to Canada. Not like those who did not come back alive either.  Just like the rest of you, trying to figure out, in history, 30 years later, where my niche, my place in the pecking order is.  <br><br>
I don't think I deserved the smack in the face from you, but perhaps I did.  I really don't know whether to tell you to go to hell or thank you. Can you meet me half way and explain? Did I hit a nerve and can you cop to it, or did I miss by a mile?  Talk to me. The responses that I have received have all been quite different than yours, is one of us out of step, or perhaps, we both don't know the dance... <br><br>
doc
